condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Para D and Project Agreement Section E | Description :The Borrower shall cause IIGF to: 1)implement the ESMF, RPF and IPPF referred to in the OM with respect to all of its operations (including, but not limited to, anyWB-Supported IIGF-project and any TA Activity); and 2) provide to the WB, on a timely basis as part of each Project Report, areport on the status and performance of the implementation of the ESMF, RPF and IPPF. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.B.2; Project Agreement, Schedule Sec I.B.1 | Description :IGF shall applyin all of its operations (including, but not limited to the WB-Supported IIGF Guarantees), the Operations Manual, including theEnvironmental and Social Management Framework (ESMF), acceptable to the Borrower and the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Section 2.A.1; Project Agreement, Section 2.A. | Description :The Borrower shall monitor &evaluate Project progress and prepare Project Reports in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.08 of the General Conditionsand on the basis of the indicators agreed with the WB. Project Reports prepared by IIGF will cover the period of one calendarquarter, and will be provided to the WB not later than 45 days after the end of the period covered by such report. | Frequency:Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Section 2.B.3; Project Agreement, Section II.B.3 | Description :The Borrower shall cause IIGF tohave its Financial Statements audited in accordance with the provisions of Sec 5.09(b) of the General Conditions using independentauditors acceptable to the WB and Borrower. Each audit of the Financial Statements shall cover the period of 1-fiscal year of theBorrower. The AFS for each such period shall be furnished to WB not later than six months. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Schedule, Section I.A, paragraph 1(b) | Description :IIGF shall engage by the earlier of thefirst date on which IIGF initiates appraisal of a WB-Supported IIGF-project & the date which is 1 year after Effectiveness Date &thereafter maintain until completion of the Project (or until IIGF has built sufficient internal capacity), a consultant firm tooutsource appraisal of IIGF-projects, with qualification & terms of reference acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :12-Jun-2014
